radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated, mainly fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 17 mm in diameter with an appendicolith at the base of the appendix, hyperenhancement of the appendiceal wall, and periappendiceal fat stranding. There is no evidence of abscess formation or perforation. The lung bases are clear bilaterally. The liver is slightly fatty without focal lesions. The gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No free air.
